.TH "intel_psr_update" 9 "intel_psr_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_psr_update \- Update PSR state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" intel_psr_update
.BI "(struct intel_dp *intel_dp "  ","
.BI "const struct intel_crtc_state *crtc_state "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_connector_state *conn_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "intel_dp" 12
Intel DP
.IP "crtc_state" 12
new CRTC state
.IP "conn_state" 12
new CONNECTOR state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This functions will update PSR states, disabling, enabling or switching PSR
version when executing fastsets. For full modeset, \fBintel_psr_disable\fP and
\fBintel_psr_enable\fP should be called instead.
